Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Here is my meme picture

My mental change during assessment 

library(tidyverse)
library(magick)

#We read two images first
confidence <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DQJH8RJX4AA4i05?format=jpg&name=large") %>% image_resize("600x600")

crying <- image_read("https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2016/03/29/ap_090911089838_sq-3271237f28995f6530d9634ff27228cae88e3440-s900-c85.webp") %>% image_resize("600x600")

#creating the text images

textc <- image_blank(width = 600, height = 600, color = "#ffffff") %>% 
  image_annotate(text = "Finish my\nRmarkdown answer sheet\nbefore the last minute", 
                 color = "#f54242",
                 size = 50,
                 gravity = "center")

textd <- image_blank(width = 600, height = 600, color = "#000000") %>% 
  image_annotate(text = "Can't knit it to html\ndue to unknown error", 
                 color = "#ffffff",
                 size = 50,
                 gravity = "center")

#Put them together
confident <- image_append(c(confidence,textc),stack = FALSE)

cry <- image_append(c(crying,textd),stack = FALSE)

jordan_meme <- image_append(c(confident,cry), stack = TRUE) %>% 
  image_scale(600)

#Save the meme

image_write(jordan_meme, "my_meme.png")
